Vice President Mike Pence met with Turkish Prime Minister Binali Yildirim at the White House to reaffirm the strategic partnership between the United States and Turkey. They expressed hope for improved relations and agreed on the need for constructive dialogue on bilateral challenges. Both countries emphasized their mutual interest in stability and security in the Middle East and committed to further consultations. Pence thanked Turkey for its contributions to global security and the fight against ISIS, while also expressing concern over the arrests of American citizens, journalists, and civil society members under the state of emergency. He urged transparency and due process in resolving their cases.